card0.name: Pikachu
card0.description: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

card1.name: Charizard
card1.description: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

card2.name: Bulbasaur
card2.description: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this Pokémon.

card3.name: Squirtle
card3.description: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

card4.name: Caterpie
card4.description: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

card5.name: Weedle
card5.description: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.

card6.name: Pidgey
card6.description: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

card7.name: Rattata
card7.description: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

card8.name: Spearow
card8.description: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

card9.name: Ekans
card9.description: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.

card10.name: Sandslash
card10.description: The drier the area Sandslash lives in, the harder and smoother the Pokémon’s spikes will feel when touched.

card11.name: Darkrai
card11.description: It chases people and Pokémon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.

card12.name: Mew
card12.description: When viewed through a microscope, this Pokémon’s short, fine, delicate hair can be seen.

card13.name: Giratina
card13.description: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

card14.name: Metagross
card14.description: Because the magnetic powers of these Pokémon get stronger in freezing temperatures, Metagross living on snowy mountains are full of energy.

card15.name: Articuno
card15.description: This legendary bird Pokémon can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

card16.name: Tyranitar
card16.description: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It is so insolent that it doesn’t care about others.

card17.name: Sceptile
card17.description: The leaves growing on Sceptile’s body are very sharp edged. This Pokémon is very agile—it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.

card18.name: Delphox
card18.description: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

card19.name: Luxray
card19.description: It can see clearly through walls to track down its prey and seek its lost young.

card20.name: Perrserker
card20.description: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.

card21.name: Hydreigon
card21.description: Only the central head has a brain. It is very intelligent, but it thinks only of destruction.

card22.name: Kyogre
card22.description: Through Primal Reversion and with nature’s full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.

card23.name: Koffing
card23.description: Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.

card24.name: Garchomp
card24.description: It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.

card25.name: Iron Thorns
card25.description: It has some similarities to a Pokémon introduced in a dubious magazine as a Tyranitar from one billion years into the future.

card26.name: Glaceon
card26.description: It can control its body temperature at will. This enables it to freeze the moisture in the atmosphere, creating flurries of diamond dust.

card27.name: Hitmonlee
card27.description: This amazing Pokémon has an awesome sense of balance. It can kick in succession from any position.

card28.name: Meditite
card28.description: It never skips its daily yoga training. It heightens its inner strength through meditation.
